= Line Cracker =
#context: sop
#type: node

"""Fractures ground geometry along a projected polyline path."""

== Overview ==

Line Cracker projects a polyline onto the X/Z plane and uses it as a fracture boundary for the input ground geometry. Both open and closed polylines are supported.

The fracture iteratively refines the cut to better match the input line shape.

@inputs

Ground:
    The geometry to fracture. Does not need to be flat.

Single Primitive Poly Line:
    The polyline used as the fracture boundary. Must be a single primitive.

@parameters

Iterations:
    #id: iterations
    Number of refinement iterations. Higher values produce a closer match to the input polyline.

Iteration Threshold:
    #id: iteration_threshold
    Minimum segment length. Segments shorter than this are skipped to avoid extremely small pieces.

Clean Zero Plane:
    #id: clean_zero_plane
    Removes degenerate faces on the zero plane after fracturing.

Clean Threshold:
    #id: clean_threshold
    Distance threshold for zero-plane face removal.

== Pieces ==

Create Interior Surfaces:
    #id: createinteriorsurfaces
    Generates capping surfaces along the fracture cuts.

Name Attribute:
    #id: namemethod
    Whether to overwrite or append to the existing `name` primitive attribute.

Name Prefix:
    #id: nameprefix
    Prefix for generated piece names. Default: `piece`.

Compute Interior Normals:
    #id: computeinteriornormals
    Recomputes normals on interior (cut) surfaces.

Interior Cusp Angle:
    #id: interiorcuspangle
    Cusp angle threshold for interior normal computation.

Exterior Normals:
    #id: computeexteriornormals
    Normal handling for exterior surfaces: preserve existing, recompute, or skip.

== Output Attributes ==

Output Primitive Piece:
    #id: outputpieceattrib
    Writes a primitive attribute identifying which piece each polygon belongs to.

Output Interior Group:
    #id: outputinteriorgroup
    Creates a primitive group containing interior (cut) faces.

Output Exterior Group:
    #id: outputexteriorgroup
    Creates a primitive group containing exterior faces.

Copy Cell Point Attributes:
    #id: copycellattribs
    Copies attributes from the fracture cell points to piece points and primitives.
